I’m running the New York City Marathon to raise funds for Holocaust survivors through the nonprofit @bluecard1934, who are currently living below the poverty line.

Holocaust survivors are currently:

-Aged between 78-105 years old
-77% are women
-70% live alone
-67% cannot leave their homes without -assistance
-50% of survivors currently live 200% below the federal poverty line

Link in bio if you resonate with this cause and are interested in donating to provide direct financial assistance to these survivors. Much love 💙

Photo dump from Sony Kando ’23

I just got home from my second Kando trip this week in Snowbird, Utah. Between learning new things, being in nature, sharing ideas with creatives from around the world, and spending time with close friends, this experience left me feeling invigorated and grateful to be a part of the Sony Alpha Collective.

camera: Sony A7CR (just released!)
lenses: 24mm f2.8, 35mm f1.4, and 50mm f2.5.
@Sonyalpha #sonypartner #sonykandotrip
Taking photos??..on a lens filled with iced tea? @goldpeak #shotwithgoldpeak

Here are the stills from my video (check it out if you missed it) of taking photos with the @goldpeak lens, which is a lens filled with iced tea (literally) to give a 'golden hour' effect any time of the day.

Having any liquid moving around in a lens while shooting definitely had its challenges, but it was fun to play into the effects of it and forced me to get a little creative. #shotwithgoldpeak

today marks 1 month until the NEW YORK CITY MARATHON BABY

Training so far has been a challenge for me, both mentally and physically, but what keeps me going is having a goal to works towards, and doing so for a cause very important to me: @bluecard1934, which is a non profit that provides direct financial assistance to holocaust survivors currently living below the poverty line.

Holocaust Survivors are currently:
-between 78-105 years old
-77% are women
-70% live alone
-67% can not leave their homes without assistance
-50% of survivors currently live 200% below the federal poverty line

Thank you SO much to everyone who has already donated so far. We’ve reached our fundraising goal!
Also special thanks to my pals for helping me shoot these marathon photos/videos:
Photos and video by @maxwellswift

Tompkin’s Dog Parade 2023 🦴

animal eye auto focus feature on my camera was crucial to lock focus on some of these shots: captured on my @sonyalpha A1 w/ 35mm 1.4  and 14mm 1.8 lenses

Yesterday, I became a marathoner. This was the most difficult thing I’ve ever done. The journey has been a testament to what hard work and determination can achieve, and I will forever be grateful for this deeply emotional, mental, and physical experience.

Being a part of the @nycmarathon has me feeling more proud than ever to be a New Yorker. The race encapsulates the spirit and energy of New York City itself: diverse, vibrant, challenging, and ultimately, a big celebration of human achievement.

Honored to run this thing in support of @bluecard1934: a non profit that provides direct financial assistance to holocaust survivors currently living below the poverty line.

Thank you everyone again to my friends, family, and everyone else: I’m grateful for your support whether you messaged me words of encouragement, cheered, high-fived, donated, etc….it means a lot to me as this was a really big deal for me. Also, BIG congrats to all the other marathon runners out there.

Also, shoutout to my photographer friends for capturing these photos of me: @watchingnewyork, @scoboco, @fritzbacon, @billydeee.
